##Wuhan family of Seven anti-plague | wait, I want to donate plasma

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Citizens of Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan, Ms. Xia

The paper's reporter, Sasha Szeto, collates

Xia Lives in Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan. There are seven people in her family: Her in-laws, her parents, her husband, and her three-year-old child. Earlier, the www.thepaper.cn  reported that seven members of her family were suspected to have contracted new coronary pneumonia.

Her in-laws, her husband has been found lung infection or disease, was admitted to the Ninth Hospital in Wuhan Isolation Ward. Her parents, who also had lung infections, had been treated at a Central Hospital in Wuhan. Subsequently, her in-laws, husband and mother tested positive for the new coronavirus nucleic acid. On the morning of February 4, Xia's father "sudden serious illness" rescue invalid death, she and her family could not see his father one last time.

On February 14, Ms. Xia said her father-in-law's health was not good, but still beat the virus, the same day has been discharged home. Her three-year-old's nucleic acid test also turned negative, if again negative, can also be discharged.

Ms Xia's father-in-law was discharged from hospital. Ms Xia provided 00:11

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xia is undergoing intravenous infusion treatment

Xia said she wanted to get better quickly to inspire other patients. If recovered and released, she and her husband would like to donate plasma for other patients.

The paper will continue to keep a diary of what Xia's family went through during the treatment.

Here is MS Xia's diary:

Friday, February 14th, sunny

Today is my 11th day in the hospital, my physical signs are quite stable.

In the morning, the doctor said, I will go to check again in a couple of days, and then see how the body recovers. The nurse checks oxygen saturation, heart rate, and temperature three or four times a day. All my other readings were normal, except for my heart rate, occasional back pain, and a sore throat when I woke up early.

Today's breakfast, friends sent her hand-made cake, but also sent a car pct. I had a good breakfast and felt full of energy.

Since therapy, I think it's really important to eat well. When I am hungry, I am in bad spirits. I feel strong after eating. The doctor said it's a wasting disease, so nutrition is important.

Today, the Children's hospital said my baby nucleic acid negative, if the test is negative again, the baby can be discharged, I see the dawn again! Come on, I got ta get better too. Pick up darling and go home.

I hope I get better soon, to cheer up the other patients. When I'm ready, I want to donate plasma, and so does my husband.

Today the biggest good news is, my father-in-law nucleic acid test double Yin, has been discharged home!

February 14,2020
